## palantir-mini v0.2 adoption

- `@palantirKC/claude-schemas` pinned at `0.2.x` via `package.json#peerDependencies`.
  `pm-verify` gates on this compatibility range.
- `palantir-mini@0.2.0` plugin provides the `mcp__palantir-mini__*` tool suite
  via the plugin-bundled MCP server — no per-project `.mcp.json` needed.
- `.claude/managed-settings.d/50-palantir-mini.json` is the Layer-1 RBAC fragment
  that grants plugin MCP tools + event-log write + `src/generated/` write.
- `.palantir-mini/session/events.jsonl` is the append-only event log. Never
  rewrite, reorder, or truncate per rule 10.
- `src/generated/` is owned exclusively by `pm-codegen`. Never hand-edit per
  rule 11 — regenerate from `ontology/` instead.

## Next steps

1. `/pm-init` — emits the first `session_started` event.
2. Define project ontology under `ontology/*.ts`.
3. `/pm-codegen` — generate `src/generated/` from ontology.
4. `/pm-verify` — 4-phase validation pipeline (Design + Compile + Runtime + Post-Write).

## Claude authority chain

`meaning → ontology → contracts → runtime → artifacts → audit/learn`.

Shared project truth lives in `ontology/`, `src/`, and `tests/`.
`.claude/rules/` overlays, if any, are Claude-local only.
